&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hounslow and Richmond Community Healthcare NHS Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hounslow Community Learning Disability Team (CLDT)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: &lt;/strong&gt;Community Staff Nurse (Registered Nurse)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Base: Heart of Hounslow Centre for Health&lt;/strong&gt; Hounslow, TW3 3EL&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Post: &lt;/strong&gt;Community Staff Nurse (Community learning Disability Team)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5: &lt;/strong&gt;£28,691 – £35,207 includes outer London weighting&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: &lt;/strong&gt;37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you ready for a challenge?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a dynamic, innovative and enthusiastic community staff nurse to join our multidisciplinary team for adults with learning disabilities. This post is particularly suited to a newly/recently qualified RNLD.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Registered Nurse (RNLD, Registered Mental Health Nurse or RNA/RGN)&lt;/strong&gt;, you will be based in Hounslow and will work across the London Borough of Hounslow. Some out of Borough work is also part of this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hounslow is a vibrant London Borough with 305,000 residents, over 140 languages spoken and 36% of the populations are from ethnic minority communities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With miles of river, canals, wildlife preserves and open spaces, Hounslow has a lot to celebrate. Covering 23 square miles, stretching from Heathrow Airport in the west to Chiswick in the east, Hounslow is one of the capital&#39;s most diverse boroughs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The borough features modern housing estates, quiet suburbs, green belt villages like Heston and bustling and fashionable cosmopolitan districts such as Chiswick.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our central focus is to have the Service User and their family at the core of what we do. We are deeply committed to delivering on the wider learning disability agenda and other relevant health and social care legislation and guidance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Registered Nurse, you will receive active support and guidance from your peers and senior colleagues. The Trust is also committed to your professional development, offering flexible learning opportunities via the professional development processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in this role, then we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For informal enquiries please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Neena Kochhar, Senior Community Nurse on (office) 020 86145410&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Neena Kochhar, Senior Nurse Adult Learning Disabiliy Team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address hrch.haldht@nhs.net Telephone numbe r02086145410&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If Neena cannot be contacted please contact Malcolm Philp Interim manager Hounslow Adult LD Team on the same number. Our administration team will ensure someone gets back to you.&lt;/p&gt;
